OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F309A1784285298
OL,3,CItalian officials jailed over 2018
OL,4,CGenoa bridge collapse
OL,6,FAutostrade and its subsidiary reached
OL,7,Fa deal on corporate liability earlier
OL,8,Fin the proceedings, paying roughly 30
OL,9,Fmillion euros ($34 million) in
OL,10,Ffinancial penalties. The agreement
OL,11,Fspared the companies from a trial as
OL,12,Fcorporate defendants and potentially
OL,13,Fmuch harsher sanctions, including
OL,14,Fexclusion from public contracts.
OL,16,FThe settlements were reached after the
OL,17,Fcompanies adopted new compliance
OL,18,Fprocedures aimed at preventing similar
OL,19,Faccidents, and after victims were
OL,20,Fcompensated.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
